topic.title: SWT - Subsidence and Aquifer-System Compaction Package for Water-Table Aquifers

para.text: SWT - Subsidence and Aquifer-System Compaction Package for Water-Table Aquifers

table.style: width:auto; cell-padding:2px; cell-spacing:2px; page-break-inside:auto; border-width:1px; border-spacing:2px; cell-border-width:1px; border-color:#000000; border-style:raised-color; background-color:none; head-row-background-color:none; alt-row-background-color:none;

para.text: SWT simulates vertical compaction in models of regional groundwater flow. The program simulates groundwater storage changes and compaction in discontinuous interbeds or in extensive confining units, accounting for stress-dependent changes in storage properties. Several features of the program make it useful for application in shallow, unconfined flow systems. Geostatic stress can be treated as a function of water-table elevation, and compaction is a function of computed changes in effective stress at the bottom of a model layer. Thickness of compressible sediments in an unconfined model layer can vary in proportion to saturated thickness.

para.link: Leake, S.A., and Galloway, D.L., 2007, MODFLOW ground-water model -- User guide to the Subsidence and Aquifer-System Compaction Package (SUB-WT) for Water-Table Aquifers: U.S. Geological Survey Techniques and Methods, Book 6, Chap. A23, 42 p.

para.text: Input for the SUB-WT Package is read from the file that has the type

in the name file. Optional variables are shown in brackets. All single-valued variables in data items 1, 3, 16, and 17, and layer assignments for systems of interbeds in data item 2 are read in free format. Data items 1, 2, 3, and 16 consist of, at most, one record. Two-dimensional arrays in data items 4
15 are read with MODFLOW utility array readers
. For instructions on use of array readers, refer to Harbaugh and others (2000) or Harbaugh (2005).

para.text: ISWTCB is a flag and unit number.

li.text: If ISWTCB > 0, it is the unit number to which cell-by-cell flow terms will be written when “SAVE BUDGET” or a non-zero value for
is specified in MODFLOW Output Control (for example, Harbaugh and others, 2000, p. 52–55).
If ISWTCB ≤ 0, cell-by-cell flow terms will not be recorded.

li.text: If ISWTOC > 0, it is the number of repetitions of item 17 to be read, each repetition of which defines a set of times steps and associated flags for printing and saving subsidence, compaction by layer, compaction by interbed system, vertical displacement, preconsolidation stress, change in preconsolidation stress, geostatic stress, change in geostatic stress, effective stress, change in effective stress, void ratio, thickness of interbeds, and layer-center elevation.
If ISWTOC

0, subsidence, compaction, vertical displacement, preconsolidation stress, change in preconsolidation stress, geostatic stress, change in geostatic stress, effective stress, change in effective stress, void ratio, thickness of interbeds, and layer-center elevation will not be printed or saved.

para.text: NSYSTM is the number of systems of interbeds.

para.text: ITHK is a flag to determine how thicknesses of compressible sediments vary in response to changes in saturated thickness.

li.text: If ITHK
0, thickness of compressible sediments is constant.
If ITHK > 0, thickness of compressible sediments varies in response to changes in saturated thickness.

para.text: IVOID is a flag to determine how void ratios of compressible sediments vary in response to changes in saturated thickness.

li.text: If IVOID
0, void ratio will be treated as a constant.
If IVOID > 0, void ratio will be treated as a variable.

para.text: ISTPCS is a flag to determine how initial preconsolidation stress will be obtained.

li.text: If ISTPCS
¹
0, an array of offset values will be read in for each model layer. The offset values will be added to the initial effective stress to get initial preconsolidation stress.
If ISTPCS = 0, an array with initial preconsolidation stress values will be read in.

para.text: ICRCC is a flag to determine how recompression and compression indices will be obtained.

li.text: If ICRCC
¹
0, arrays of elastic specific storage and inelastic skeletal specific storage will be read for each system of interbeds. The recompression index and compression index will not be read.

If ICRCC = 0, arrays of recompression index and compression index will be read for each system of interbeds. Elastic skeletal specific storage and inelastic skeletal specific storage will not be read.
